        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This study shows that the hevin protein produced by astrocytes is found in the synaptic cleft in the adult rat cerebal cortex.\n\n8/8/2017 Pim\n- SPRL1_RAT, Hevin, SPARC-like 1, MAST 9 is a known component of the ECM.. Experimental description: \"Electron microscopic immunocytochemistry was performed on the adult rat cerebral cortex.\" Figure legend, P. 173" ;
